{
  "answer": "The following works in the corpus mention specific Indian rivers (primarily the Ganges/Gaṅgā, Yamunā/Jumna, and Sarasvatī). No mentions were found for other major rivers such as the Indus, Godāvarī, Narmadā, or Brahmaputra.[^1]\n\n**Āṅgirasa Smṛti** (unknown-angirasa-smrti-2bf9d1): Mentions the Ganges (as *jāhnavītīraṃ*, \"the bank of the Ganges\").[^2]\n\n**Nouveau traité d'économie: VOL I** (charles-dunoyer-nouveau-traite-deconomie-vol-i-6da8ce): Mentions the Ganges (twice, as a geographical boundary and in a reference to Indian customs).[^3][^4]\n\n**Traité de Législation: VOL II** (charles-comte-traite-de-legislation-vol-ii-20331d): Mentions the Ganges (as a geographical boundary of the Caucasian race).[^5]\n\n**Viṣṇu Smṛti** (unknown-visnu-smrti-27f0d8): Mentions the Ganges (multiple times, e.g., for ritual immersion and as a holy site) and the Yamunā.[^6][^7]\n\n**Manusmṛti** (unknown-manusmrti-347b76): Mentions the Sarasvatī (as a divine river defining the Brahmāvarta region).[^8]\n\n**Vīramitrodaya** (unknown-viramitrodaya-d4b632): Mentions the Gaṅgā and Yamunā (in the compound *Gaṅgāyamunam*).[^9]\n\n[^1]: Based on targeted searches across the English translations in the corpus for \"Ganges\", \"Yamuna\", \"Indus\", \"Godavari\", \"Narmada\", \"Sarasvati\", \"Jumna\", and \"Brahmaputra\".\n\n[^2]: [Āṅgirasa Smṛti, Chapter 1, paragraph p-543a9d](/works/unknown-angirasa-smrti-2bf9d1/01/translation/#p-543a9d).\n\n[^3]: [Nouveau traité d'économie: VOL I, Chapter 2, paragraph p-6ac2b8](/works/charles-dunoyer-nouveau-traite-deconomie-vol-i-6da8ce/02-i-influence-de-la-race-sur-la-liberte/translation/#p-6ac2b8).\n\n[^4]: [Nouveau traité d'économie: VOL I, Chapter 3, paragraph p-1f97b0](/works/charles-dunoyer-nouveau-traite-deconomie-vol-i-6da8ce/03-ii-influence-des-circonstances-exterieures-sur-la-/translation/#p-1f97b0).\n\n[^5]: [Traité de Législation: VOL II, Chapter 3, paragraph p-f0c315](/works/charles-comte-traite-de-legislation-vol-ii-20331d/03-des-diverses-especes-ou-varietes-dont-se-compose-l/translation/#p-f0c315).\n\n[^6]: [Viṣṇu Smṛti, Chapter 19, paragraph p-eaf423](/works/unknown-visnu-smrti-27f0d8/19/translation/#p-eaf423).\n\n[^7]: [Viṣṇu Smṛti, Chapter 85, paragraph p-56eece](/works/unknown-visnu-smrti-27f0d8/85/translation/#p-56eece).\n\n[^8]: [Manusmṛti, Chapter 2, paragraph p-a9e644](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/02/translation/#p-a9e644).\n\n[^9]: [Vīramitrodaya, Chapter 1, paragraph p-4c32c7](/works/unknown-viramitrodaya-d4b632/01/translation/#p-4c32c7).",
